AWS EFS:
  Create new EFS
      Name: Assign a name (e.g., my-efs).
      VPC: Select your VPC.
      Availability Zones: Choose subnets (recommended: all AZs for high availability).
      
 2. Configure Security Groups

      Create or Update Security Group:
      Go to EC2 > Security Groups > Create security group.
      Add an inbound rule for NFS:
      Type: NFS (port 2049).
      Protocol: TCP.
      Source: Security group of your EC2 instances or a specific CIDR block.



(1) configartion on EC2 

        Create New Directory:
           cd /home/ubuntu
           mkdir newstorage
           cd /home/ubuntu/newstorage
        
        Nfs Configration:
           sudo vim /etc/fstab
                   fs-0934333a2a7d94e31.efs.us-east-1.amazonaws.com:/ /home/ubuntu/newstorage nfs4 defaults,_netdev 0 0
        
           sudo mount -a
           sudo systemctl daemon-reload
           sudo systemctl restart remote-fs.target
           
           lsblk
           df -h
